ATTRIBUTION / SOURCE NOTICE
================================================================================

This project is an interactive German learning website that adapts and builds
upon the course materials of:

    "Data Science 2 – Grundlagen der Statistik und experimentelles Design"
    by Dr. Saskia Otto, Universität Hamburg
    https://saskiaotto.github.io/uham-bio-data-science-2/
    (course hub: https://dsb-start.de/courses/ds2.html)

The original course materials are licensed under
Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-SA 4.0).

CHANGES MADE: The statistical concepts, structure, and example datasets
(e.g. Vogelzug, Iris, Daphnia, Lachs, Mendel) follow the original course.
This adaptation rewrites the content as original German explanatory prose with
custom interactive visualisations and self-checks; it is not a verbatim copy.

In accordance with the ShareAlike term, THIS adaptation is likewise licensed
under CC BY-SA 4.0. You are free to share and adapt it, for any purpose, as long
as you give appropriate credit (to both Dr. Saskia Otto for the original course
and to this project) and distribute your contributions under the same license.

